g.text: Game Jams: The most fun you can have while programming
Programming is a lot of fun. It’s an awesome feeling when your code compiles without errors, the app passes all the
tests, and runs without any (noticeable) bugs. It’s an awesome feeling even if you are working on a boring enterprise
app. You made the primitive machine under your keyboard
something. If that isn’t amazing I don’t know what is.
Now take the satisfaction you get when you produce working code and multiply it by 100. This is how awesome it feels
when you are making a game.
